data.current_description:
**This endpoint allows you to retrieve the branded link associated with a subuser.**

Link branding can be associated with subusers from the parent account. This functionality allows subusers to send mail using their parent's link branding. To associate link branding, the parent account must first create a branded link and then validate it. The parent may then associate that branded link with a subuser via the API or the [Subuser Management page of the Twilio SendGrid App](https://app.sendgrid.com/settings/subusers).
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves the branded link associated with a specified subuser. Link branding allows subusers to send mail using their parent account's branded links. The parent account must first create and validate a branded link before associating it with a subuser via the API or Subuser Management page. Requires the subuser ID as a query parameter. Returns the branded link configuration object for that subuser, or an error if no link is associated.
data.reasoning: While the summary is clear, the description lacks specific details about required inputs (subuser ID parameter) and expected outputs (what the response contains). Added clarification about the required query parameter and the structure of the response to improve AI agent interpretability for determining when and how to invoke this operation.

data.current_summary: Disassociate a branded link from a subuser
data.current_description:
**This endpoint allows you to take a branded link away from a subuser.**

Link branding can be associated with subusers from the parent account. This functionality allows subusers to send mail using their parent's link branding. To associate link branding, the parent account must first create a branded link and validate it. The parent may then associate that branded link with a subuser via the API or the [Subuser Management page of the Twilio SendGrid App](https://app.sendgrid.com/settings/subusers).

Your request will receive a response with a 204 status code if the disassociation was successful.
data.description_suggestion: Removes the branded link association from a specified subuser. After disassociation, the subuser will no longer use the parent account's branded link for email delivery. Requires the subuser ID as a query parameter. Returns a 204 No Content status code on successful disassociation. The subuser will revert to using default SendGrid-branded links after this operation.
data.reasoning: The summary is clear and action-oriented, but the description lacks specific input requirements (subuser ID parameter) and complete output details. You can submit this request as one of your subusers if you include their ID in the `on-behalf-of` header in the request.

data.current_description:
**This endpoint allows you to delete a branded link.**

Your request will receive a response with a 204 status code if the deletion was successful. The call does not return the link's details, so if you wish to record these make sure you call the  "Retrieve a branded link" endpoint *before* you request its deletion.

You can submit this request as one of your subusers if you include their ID in the `on-behalf-of` header in the request.
data.description_suggestion: Deletes a branded link by ID. Returns a 204 No Content status code on successful deletion with no response body. The branded link resource is permanently removed and can no longer be used for email link tracking. If you need to preserve the link's configuration details, retrieve them before deletion. You can submit this request on behalf of a subuser by including their ID in the `on-behalf-of` header.
